{"pageProps":{"note":{"id":"ohfk4ao5xo2zijxcchgutju","title":"Random Projections","desc":"","updated":1646305736950,"created":1646305425516,"custom":{},"fname":"science.math.Functional Analysis.High Dimensional Neighborhood Search.Random Projections","type":"note","vault":{"fsPath":"vault"},"contentHash":"2ff57ac3e6da845ce3d674df75feb925","links":[{"type":"wiki","from":{"fname":"science.math.Functional Analysis.High Dimensional Neighborhood Search.Random Projections","id":"ohfk4ao5xo2zijxcchgutju","vaultName":"vault"},"value":"science.stats.Unsupervised Learning.KNN.Locality Sensitive Hashing","alias":"science.stats.Unsupervised Learning.KNN.Locality Sensitive Hashing","position":{"start":{"line":11,"column":1,"offset":749},"end":{"line":11,"column":71,"offset":819},"indent":[]},"xvault":false,"sameFile":false,"to":{"fname":"science.stats.Unsupervised Learning.KNN.Locality Sensitive Hashing"}},{"from":{"fname":"engineering.system_design.ML System Design.Recommender Systems","vaultName":"vault"},"type":"backlink","position":{"start":{"line":47,"column":1,"offset":1033},"end":{"line":47,"column":93,"offset":1125},"indent":[]},"value":"science.math.Functional Analysis.High Dimensional Neighborhood Search.Random Projections","alias":"science.math.Functional Analysis.High Dimensional Neighborhood Search.Random Projections"},{"from":{"fname":"science.stats.Unsupervised Learning.KNN","vaultName":"vault"},"type":"backlink","position":{"start":{"line":22,"column":1,"offset":856},"end":{"line":22,"column":93,"offset":948},"indent":[]},"value":"science.math.Functional Analysis.High Dimensional Neighborhood Search.Random Projections","alias":"science.math.Functional Analysis.High Dimensional Neighborhood Search.Random Projections"},{"from":{"fname":"science.stats.Unsupervised Learning.KNN.Locality Sensitive Hashing","vaultName":"vault"},"type":"backlink","position":{"start":{"line":12,"column":12,"offset":482},"end":{"line":12,"column":104,"offset":574},"indent":[]},"value":"science.math.Functional Analysis.High Dimensional Neighborhood Search.Random Projections","alias":"science.math.Functional Analysis.High Dimensional Neighborhood Search.Random Projections"}],"anchors":{},"children":[],"parent":"q6bc1dvnjytciisll1b9uh2","data":{}},"body":"<h1 id=\"random-projections\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#random-projections\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>Random Projections</h1>\n<p>According to the <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Johnson%E2%80%93Lindenstrauss_lemma\">Johnson- Lindenstrauss Lemma</a> </p>\n<pre><code>In mathematics, the Johnson–Lindenstrauss lemma is a result named after William B. Johnson and Joram Lindenstrauss concerning low-distortion embeddings of points from high-dimensional into low-dimensional Euclidean space. The lemma states that a set of points in a high-dimensional space can be embedded into a space of much lower dimension in such a way that distances between the points are nearly preserved. The map used for the embedding is at least Lipschitz, and can even be taken to be an orthogonal projection.\n</code></pre>\n<p>So if we use low-dim random projection, the distances between the points are likely to be preserved.</p>\n<p><a href=\"/PublicPersonalKnowledgeBase/notes/gzl1o6b3ga4ho10waqx2xsd\">Locality Sensitive Hashing</a></p>\n<hr>\n<strong>Backlinks</strong>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"/PublicPersonalKnowledgeBase/notes/QE1BddXlccbyYN1avaB4M\">Recommender Systems</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/PublicPersonalKnowledgeBase/notes/x6WJBarY2rinq6LZVpoAE\">KNN</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/PublicPersonalKnowledgeBase/notes/gzl1o6b3ga4ho10waqx2xsd\">Locality Sensitive Hashing</a></li>\n</ul>","noteIndex":{"id":"wn8PE1RhG0znK1alrGFYv","title":"Root","desc":"","updated":1647507231129,"created":1631901573363,"custom":{"nav_order":0,"permalink":"/"},"fname":"root","type":"note","vault":{"fsPath":"vault"},"contentHash":"db285659ccac8b133c384de1e